## Telegram (outbound)

- **Bot token:** `$TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` from `_shared/bridge/envs/{{AGENT_DIR}}.env`
- **Allow-list user ID:** `$ALLOWED_USER_ID` (Ricky's Telegram ID; messages from any other `from.id` are refused by the bridge)
- **Existing wrapper:** `builds/customer-service/modules/enquiry/lib/telegram-client.js`
- **Rich cards:** `builds/customer-service/modules/enquiry/lib/card-formatter.js`
- **4096-char limit per message** ‚Äî longer replies must split

## Codex (Agent tool, build path)

- **Subagent type:** `codex:codex-rescue`
- **Invocation:** Use the `Agent` tool with `subagent_type: "codex:codex-rescue"` and a self-contained brief following the Agent Delegation Protocol.
- **Fresh per call** ‚Äî Codex has no persistent memory across invocations. Pass all context in the brief.

## Codex Desktop (manual handoff, product QA path)

- **No programmatic API.** Ricky runs it manually.
- **Handoff flow:** `/test-loop` writes a QA plan to `_shared/records/qa-plans/<project>-<ts>.md`, sends Ricky a Telegram message with the path, waits for paste-back.

